If you experience any problem while using this skill, you can contact us by email: service@lightingever.com

You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. 
There’s no need to use the switch to adjust your home light-just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo and it’s done.

There are some simple steps you need to follow to connect your Lampux Smart products with Alexa:
(1)Download the ”Lampux” app in the Android or iOS app market;
(2)Register a Lampux smart account in the ”Lampux” app;
(3)You need to have some Lampux Smart devices of LE in hand; It is required that you own a LE Lampux Smart device;
(4)Configure your devices in your “Lampux” app and change the name for your devices which will be used in “Lampux” skills;
(5)Download the Amazon ”Alexa” app from andriod, iOS or Amazon app market;
(6)Configure echo with ”Alexa” App;
(7)Search ”Lampux” Skill from the “Alexa” app skills categories;
(8)Click Enable skill of ”Lampux” , and you’ll be navigated to Lampux login page;
(9)Input your Lampux account username and password, you will be redirected to the success page;
(10)Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on kitchen light”
“Alexa, turn off kitchen light”
“Alexa, dim livingroom light”
“Alexa, brighten livingroom light”
“Alexa, set the livingroom light to 20 percent”
“Alexa, set the bedroom light to blue”
“Alexa, turn on bedroom air conditioner”
Currently this skill supports products:
Smart switch,
Smart socket,
Smart bulb......
